Nigella sativa

   [7987.jpg]
   Authority L.
   Family Magnoliopsida:Magnoliidae:Ranunculales:Ranunculaceae
   Synonyms
   Common names fennel-flower, black cumin, black caraway, gith, nutmeg
   flower, ragged lady, Roman coriander, kalonji, nigelle de Crete,
   schwarzkuemmel, nigela, garidela, cominho negro, ajenuz, aranue,
   tikur-azmud
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 7987

   Notes
   SOURCES
   Jansen P 1981 pp 76-85 [TEXT, USE]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 380 [USE]
   Duke J 1975 pp 22 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   GROWING PERIOD
   Annual herb growing 100-150 days.
   COMMON NAMES
   Black cummin, Garden nigelle, Nigelle cultivee, Quatre epices,
   Toute-epice, Cumin noir, Patte d'araignee, Schwarzkummel, Narden-samen,
   Romischer kummel, Tukur azmut, Tikur azmud, Habasudu, Abasuda, Nugi
   guracha, Gurati, Gurra, Aaf, Awosetta.
   FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonyms: N. cretica, N. indica, N. arvensis. Black cummin
   is most probably native of the Mediterranean region. The plant can
   reach a height of 70 cm. In Ethiopia, it is cultivated as a rainfed
   crop at altitudes between 1500-2500 m.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
